{
  "texts": [
    "Clinical examination of the abdomen was normal; subsequent computed tomography (CT) scan revealed a 7.7 cm, round, well-demarcated, solid and cystic mass within the tail of the pancreas.",
    "An endoscopic ultrasonography with biopsy of the lesion was performed.",
    "On histology, hematoxylin&eosin stain showed fragments of epithelial proliferation composed of polygonal cells with blandly atypical round nuclei, finely dispersed chromatin, and eosinophilic cytoplasm.",
    "One mitotic figure was seen.",
    "Immunohistochemistry for CK AE1/AE3 and synaptophysin were focally positive, whereas chromogranin and Bcl-10 were negative."
  ]
}